font.span: The dists/ folder contains only indexes and Release files. No debs.
Each <channel> folder has a Release file
that has attributes of the channel and
lists all of the indexes within that channel.
A <channel> is a collection of one or more
sub-repos. There is a sub-repos for each
The only mandatory index in a sub-repo
is the Packages file which lists the deb
package files included in the sub-repo.
The filenames will either be in the ./pool/
folder if its mirrored from the upstream repo
or ./domainPool/ if it was added to this local
There are optional indexes for app store functionality, internationalization, and relating command and files to packages that provide them.
